        <h3 class="title"><a href="http://antonymarcano.com/blog/2012/06/ghostdriver/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link: GhostDriver – Headless Selenium RemoteWebDriver">GhostDriver – Headless Selenium RemoteWebDriver</a></h3>

        <!-- story header -->
        <div class="postheader">
          <div class="postinfo">
            <p>Posted by <a href="http://antonymarcano.com/blog/author/antonymarcano/" title="Posts by AntonyMarcano ">AntonyMarcano</a> in <a href="http://antonymarcano.com/blog/category/uncategorized/" title="View all posts in Uncategorized" rel="category tag">Uncategorized</a> on June 21, 2012 </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- /story header -->

        <div class="postbody entry clearfix">
         <p>GhostDriver is a Selenium server that can be connected to via a RemoteWebDriver. It runs completely heedlessly on PhantomJS but still behaves (mostly) like a typical webkit browser. By avoiding the overhead of actually rendering the page in a GUI it can run standard Selenium tests noticeably faster and on a headless build server too. [...]</p>
        </div>
