        <h3 class="title"><a href="http://antonymarcano.com/blog/2011/06/old-favourite-more-sharks-and-delaying-critical-mass/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link: Old Favourite &#8211; More Sharks and Delaying Critical Mass">Old Favourite &#8211; More Sharks and Delaying Critical Mass</a></h3>

        <!-- story header -->
        <div class="postheader">
          <div class="postinfo">
            <p>Posted by <a href="http://antonymarcano.com/blog/author/antonymarcano/" title="Posts by AntonyMarcano ">AntonyMarcano</a> in <a href="http://antonymarcano.com/blog/category/agile-2/" title="View all posts in Agile" rel="category tag">Agile</a>, <a href="http://antonymarcano.com/blog/category/business-2/" title="View all posts in Business" rel="category tag">Business</a>, <a href="http://antonymarcano.com/blog/category/business-analysis/" title="View all posts in Business Analysis" rel="category tag">Business Analysis</a>, <a href="http://antonymarcano.com/blog/category/old-favourite/" title="View all posts in Old Favourites" rel="category tag">Old Favourites</a>, <a href="http://antonymarcano.com/blog/category/project-management-2/" title="View all posts in Project Management" rel="category tag">Project Management</a>, <a href="http://antonymarcano.com/blog/category/software-development-2/" title="View all posts in Software Development" rel="category tag">Software Development</a>, <a href="http://antonymarcano.com/blog/category/software-testing-2/" title="View all posts in Software Testing" rel="category tag">Software Testing</a> on June 7, 2011 </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- /story header -->

        <div class="postbody entry clearfix">
         <p>This article originally featured on my old blog on 19th January 2010. In a previous post I talked about Critical Mass of software. I showed how an ever-increasing cost of change resulted in it becoming more economical to completely rewrite the system than to enhance and maintain the original. I explained how this could be [...]</p>
        </div>
